0–12 March 1122","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1077–1139":"1077–1139","1098–1148":"1098–1148","1110–1137":"1110–1137","1115–Male":"1115–Deceased","–1183":"–1183","1050–Male":"1050–Deceased","–1110":"–1110","about 1070":"about 1070","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1077":"1077","1098":"1098","1183":"1183","1050":"1050","1070":"1070","1139":"1139","12. März 1122":"12 March 1122","1115":"1115","1137":"1137","1148":"1148","um 1110":"about 1110","from 1115 to 1119":"from 1115 to 1119","1122":"1122","4. Dezember 1110":"4 December 1110","Gudensberg, Hesse, Holy Roman Empire":"Gudensberg, Hesse, Holy Roman Empire","Gudensberg, Hessen-Nassau, Germany":"Gudensberg, Fritzlar, Hesse-Nassau, Prussia, Germany","Hollendin":"Khuzestan, Iran","Germany":"Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Giso","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of any of the many given names ending in <i>-gino</i>, e.g. <i>Giorgino</i>, pet form of   Giorgio  , and <i>Luigino</i>, pet form of   Luigi ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"IV.","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Vivian   and   Vivien ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Giso IV. von Gudensberg was born about 1070, in Gudensberg, Hesse, Holy Roman Empire as the son of Hrabia Giso III von Gudensberg and Countess Mathilde of Montbéliard. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Kunigunde von Bilstein. He died on 12 March 1122, in his hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"about 1070–12. März 1122":"umbes 1070–12. märts 1122","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1077–1139":"1077–1139","1098–1148":"1098–1148","1110–1137":"1110–1137","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","–1183":"–1183","1050–Male":"1050–Surnud","–1110":"–1110","about 1070":"umbes 1070","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1077":"1077","1098":"1098","1183":"1183","1050":"1050","1070":"1070","1139":"1139","12. März 1122":"12. märts 1122","1115":"1115","1137":"1137","1148":"1148","um 1110":"umbes 1110","from 1115 to 1119":"1115 kuni 1119","1122":"1122","4. Dezember 1110":"4. detsember 1110","Gudensberg, Hesse, Holy Roman Empire":"Gudensberg, Hessen, Heiliges Römisches Reich","Gudensberg, Hessen-Nassau, Germany":"Gudensberg, Kreis Fritzlar, Hessen-Nassau, Preußen, Saksamaa","Hollendin":"Khūzestān, Iraan","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"about 1070–12. März 1122":"noin 1070–12. maaliskuuta 1122","1070–1122":"1070–1122","1077–1139":"1077–1139","1098–1148":"1098–1148","1110–1137":"1110–1137","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","–1183":"–1